{
  "texts": [
    "The observed rank collapse phenomenon was first recognized in NLP, specifically when fine-tuning the pre-trained model for distinct tasks.",
    "To overcome this, a Low-Rank Adaptation method [34] is proposed by of injecting rank-decomposition matrices to transformer blocks.",
    "Drawing on this concept, we design low-rank modules to fine-tune transformer blocks in AV-DNNs based on sensory data variations.",
    "Figure6(b) presents its detailed architecture.",
    "In general, the low-rank module comprises a pair of matrices A, B, which coexist parasitically for each inherent projection weight matrix."
  ]
}